    <language>en_US</language>
    <keyword>det</keyword>
    <short_description>Matrix determinant.</short_description>
    <syntax>
        <syntax_item>res = det(x)</syntax_item>
    </syntax>
    <param_input>
        <param_input_item>
            <param_name>x</param_name>
            <param_description
      >a numeric value: scalar or square matrix (double or single)</param_description>
        </param_input_item>
    </param_input>
    <param_output>
        <param_output_item>
            <param_name>res</param_name>
            <param_description
      >real or complex number (double or single), the determinant base 10.</param_description>
        </param_output_item>
    </param_output>
    <description>
        <p>
            <b>res = det(x)</b> returns the determinant of square matrix x.
        </p>
        <p>For a</p>
        <latex>2 \times 2</latex>
        <p>matrix:</p>
        <latex
    >\det\begin{pmatrix} a &amp; b \\ c &amp; d \end{pmatrix} = ad - bc</latex>
        <p
    >For larger matrices, the determinant can be computed using cofactor expansion:</p>
        <latex>\det(A) = \sum_{j=1}^{n} (-1)^{i+j} a_{ij} M_{ij}</latex>
        <p>where</p>
        <latex>M_{ij}</latex>
        <p>is the minor of element</p>
        <latex>a_{ij}</latex>
    </description>
